<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1035,1865,1928]" box="[151,367,1901,1928]" pageId="7" pageNumber="555">
<figureCitation box="[151,227,1902,1928]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,919,943]" captionTargetBox="[172,1404,233,853]" captionTargetId="figure-17@2.[160,1428,181,895]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. The phylogenetic relationship among Drymadusini species from China inferred from the COI-ND2 concatenated fragments. Rooted by Gampsocleis sinensis, the tree was constructed by Maximum likelihood (ML) with GTR+G4+F model. Topology supports of all major nodes are indicated above branches in this order: the SH-aLRT value, and the bootstrap value." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5683474" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5683474/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="555">Figs. 1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[241,286,1902,1928]" captionStart-0="FIGURE 6" captionStart-1="FIGURE 7" captionStart-2="FIGURE 8" captionStart-3="FIGURE 9" captionStartId-0="7.[151,250,1651,1675]" captionStartId-1="8.[151,250,1694,1718]" captionStartId-2="9.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionStartId-3="10.[151,250,1901,1925]" captionTargetBox-0="[196,1390,240,1619]" captionTargetBox-1="[193,1393,638,1661]" captionTargetBox-2="[194,1375,352,1907]" captionTargetBox-3="[194,1391,187,1870]" captionTargetId-0="figure-40@7.[189,1398,234,1625]" captionTargetId-1="figure-244@8.[189,1398,630,1667]" captionTargetId-2="figure-101@9.[189,1398,345,1919]" captionTargetId-3="figure-17@10.[189,1398,181,1877]" captionTargetPageId-0="7" captionTargetPageId-1="8" captionTargetPageId-2="9" captionTargetPageId-3="10" captionText-0="FIGURE 6. Head, thorax and wings of Ptosoproctus baishishanicus sp. nov. A, B, D, E–H. male; C, I, J. female. A. face; B. head and pronotum in dorsal view; C. pronotum and tegmen in lateral view; D. thorax in ventral view; E. left tegmen in dorsal view; F, right tegmen in dorsal view; G. left tegmen in ventral view; H. right tegmen in ventral view; I. hind wings; J. tegmina. Scales: 1 mm." captionText-1="FIGURE 7. Abdominal apex of Ptosoproctus baishishanicus sp. nov. A–E. male; F–H. female. A, F. dorsal view; B. lateral view; C, G. ventral view; D. rear view; E. titillators; H. ovipositor. Scales: 1 mm." captionText-2="FIGURE 8. Body of Ptosoproctus baishishanicus sp. nov. A, B. male; C, D. female. A, C. dorsal view; B, D. lateral view. Scales: 1 cm." captionText-3="FIGURE 9. Living Ptosoproctus species. A, B. P. lanzhouensis sp. nov.; C–F. P. baishishanicus sp. nov. G. habitat of P. baishishanicus at Baishi mountain; H. Michael Lee collecting P. baishishanicus." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5683484" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5683486" figureDoi-2="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5683488" figureDoi-3="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5683490" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/5683484/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/5683486/files/figure.png" httpUri-2="https://zenodo.org/record/5683488/files/figure.png" httpUri-3="https://zenodo.org/record/5683490/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="555">6–9</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[297,367,1901,1928]" captionStart-0="FIGURE 14" captionStart-1="FIGURE 15" captionStartId-0="16.[151,250,1935,1959]" captionStartId-1="17.[151,250,1426,1450]" captionTargetBox-0="[215,1397,329,1902]" captionTargetBox-1="[201,1396,606,1395]" captionTargetId-0="figure-60@16.[189,1398,309,1912]" captionTargetId-1="figure-209@17.[189,1398,594,1399]" captionTargetPageId-0="16" captionTargetPageId-1="17" captionText-0="FIGURE 14. Time signal oscillograms. A–C. Ptosoproctus lanzhouensis sp. nov.; D–F. Ptosoproctus baishishanicus sp. nov.; G–I. Eulithoxenus emeljanovi. Dashed lines: above which are the fragment expanded in the next picture." captionText-1="FIGURE 15. Distribution map of Eulithoxenus emeljanovi and the species of genus Ptosoproctus gen. nov. The symbols with a point inside are previous records." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5683500" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5683502" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/5683500/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/5683502/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="555">14–15</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1973,2037]" lastBlockId="8.[151,1437,151,609]" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="556" pageId="7" pageNumber="555">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,297,1973,1999]" pageId="7" pageNumber="555">Description.</emphasis>
General. Body small. Head frons flat. Fastigium of vertex distinctly wider than scape of antenna (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1651,1675]" captionTargetBox="[196,1390,240,1619]" captionTargetId="figure-40@7.[189,1398,234,1625]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 6. Head, thorax and wings of Ptosoproctus baishishanicus sp. nov. A, B, D, E–H. male; C, I, J. female. A. face; B. head and pronotum in dorsal view; C. pronotum and tegmen in lateral view; D. thorax in ventral view; E. left tegmen in dorsal view; F, right tegmen in dorsal view; G. left tegmen in ventral view; H. right tegmen in ventral view; I. hind wings; J. tegmina. Scales: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5683484" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5683484/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="555">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
AB). Head dorsally with an obscure and continuous median carina. Eyes broadly round and projecting outward. Disc of pronotum both sides with a broadly obtuse concavity on middle part, anterior margin of pronotum slightly concaved and posterior margin nearly straight, median carina continuous and distinctly indicated, central transvers sulcus distinctly Chinese characters “八”-shaped, lateral carina faintly indicated; lateral lobes longer than high, with weakly humeral sinus (
<figureCitation box="[417,486,259,286]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1651,1675]" captionTargetBox="[196,1390,240,1619]" captionTargetId="figure-40@7.[189,1398,234,1625]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 6. Head, thorax and wings of Ptosoproctus baishishanicus sp. nov. A, B, D, E–H. male; C, I, J. female. A. face; B. head and pronotum in dorsal view; C. pronotum and tegmen in lateral view; D. thorax in ventral view; E. left tegmen in dorsal view; F, right tegmen in dorsal view; G. left tegmen in ventral view; H. right tegmen in ventral view; I. hind wings; J. tegmina. Scales: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5683484" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5683484/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="556">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
BC). Prosternum unarmed (
<figureCitation box="[803,895,259,286]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1651,1675]" captionTargetBox="[196,1390,240,1619]" captionTargetId="figure-40@7.[189,1398,234,1625]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 6. Head, thorax and wings of Ptosoproctus baishishanicus sp. nov. A, B, D, E–H. male; C, I, J. female. A. face; B. head and pronotum in dorsal view; C. pronotum and tegmen in lateral view; D. thorax in ventral view; E. left tegmen in dorsal view; F, right tegmen in dorsal view; G. left tegmen in ventral view; H. right tegmen in ventral view; I. hind wings; J. tegmina. Scales: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5683484" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5683484/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="556">Fig. 6D</figureCitation>
). Mesosternum with a pair of obtuse triangular lobe-shaped processes, wider than long (
<figureCitation box="[614,706,295,322]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1651,1675]" captionTargetBox="[196,1390,240,1619]" captionTargetId="figure-40@7.[189,1398,234,1625]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 6. Head, thorax and wings of Ptosoproctus baishishanicus sp. nov. A, B, D, E–H. male; C, I, J. female. A. face; B. head and pronotum in dorsal view; C. pronotum and tegmen in lateral view; D. thorax in ventral view; E. left tegmen in dorsal view; F, right tegmen in dorsal view; G. left tegmen in ventral view; H. right tegmen in ventral view; I. hind wings; J. tegmina. Scales: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5683484" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5683484/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="556">Fig. 6D</figureCitation>
). Metasternum with a pair of obtuse triangular lobe-shaped processes, extremely wider than long (
<figureCitation box="[549,639,331,358]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1651,1675]" captionTargetBox="[196,1390,240,1619]" captionTargetId="figure-40@7.[189,1398,234,1625]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 6. Head, thorax and wings of Ptosoproctus baishishanicus sp. nov. A, B, D, E–H. male; C, I, J. female. A. face; B. head and pronotum in dorsal view; C. pronotum and tegmen in lateral view; D. thorax in ventral view; E. left tegmen in dorsal view; F, right tegmen in dorsal view; G. left tegmen in ventral view; H. right tegmen in ventral view; I. hind wings; J. tegmina. Scales: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5683484" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5683484/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="556">Fig. 6D</figureCitation>
). Dorsal surface of fore coxae with 1 long spine; fore femora 1.15–1.2 times longer than pronotum, dorsally unarmed, ventrally with 0–2 internal spinules and externally unarmed, genicular lobes with 1–2 internal spinules and 1 external spinule; fore tibiae both sides with a crack-shape tympana, ventrally with 6 pair of spines, a pair at the apical. Middle femora dorsally unarmed, ventrally both sides with 0–1 spinules, genicular lobes with 1 internal spinules and 1–3 external spinules; middle tibiae ventrally with 6 pair of spines, a pair at the apical. Hind femora dorsally unarmed, ventrally with 0–4 spinules on both sides, genicular lobes with 0–1 spinules on both sides; hind tibiae dorsally with 18–27 spines on both sides and 1 pair of apical spurs, ventrally with 9–10 spines on both sides and 2 pair of apical spurs.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5683486" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5683486" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5683486/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="556" startId="8.[151,250,1694,1718]" targetBox="[193,1393,638,1661]" targetPageId="8">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,1694,1754]" pageId="8" pageNumber="556">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,277,1694,1718]" pageId="8" pageNumber="556">FIGURE 7.</emphasis>
Abdominal apex of 
<taxonomicName authority="Shen &amp; Yin &amp; Lee &amp; Liu &amp; He &amp; Wang &amp; Wang, 2021" authorityName="Shen &amp; Yin &amp; Lee &amp; Liu &amp; He &amp; Wang &amp; Wang" authorityYear="2021" box="[492,784,1694,1718]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Ptosoproctus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="556" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="baishishanicus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[492,784,1694,1718]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="556">Ptosoproctus baishishanicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[792,874,1694,1718]" pageId="8" pageNumber="556">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[792,874,1694,1718]" pageId="8" pageNumber="556" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
A–E. male; F–H. female. A, F. dorsal view; B. lateral view; C, G. ventral view; D. rear view; E. titillators; H. ovipositor. Scales: 1 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,1800,2043]" lastBlockId="9.[151,1436,151,321]" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="557" pageId="8" pageNumber="556">
Male. Tegmina brachypterous, slightly longer than pronotum, extending to 2 
<superScript attach="left" box="[1055,1068,1800,1814]" fontSize="6" pageId="8" pageNumber="556">th</superScript>
abdominal tergite posterior margin. Left tegmina ventrally with stridulatory file about 36 teeth (
<figureCitation box="[890,982,1836,1863]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1651,1675]" captionTargetBox="[196,1390,240,1619]" captionTargetId="figure-40@7.[189,1398,234,1625]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 6. Head, thorax and wings of Ptosoproctus baishishanicus sp. nov. A, B, D, E–H. male; C, I, J. female. A. face; B. head and pronotum in dorsal view; C. pronotum and tegmen in lateral view; D. thorax in ventral view; E. left tegmen in dorsal view; F, right tegmen in dorsal view; G. left tegmen in ventral view; H. right tegmen in ventral view; I. hind wings; J. tegmina. Scales: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5683484" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5683484/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="556">Fig. 6G</figureCitation>
). Right tegmina ventrally with vestigial stridulatory file about 28 teeth (
<figureCitation box="[505,595,1872,1899]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1651,1675]" captionTargetBox="[196,1390,240,1619]" captionTargetId="figure-40@7.[189,1398,234,1625]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 6. Head, thorax and wings of Ptosoproctus baishishanicus sp. nov. A, B, D, E–H. male; C, I, J. female. A. face; B. head and pronotum in dorsal view; C. pronotum and tegmen in lateral view; D. thorax in ventral view; E. left tegmen in dorsal view; F, right tegmen in dorsal view; G. left tegmen in ventral view; H. right tegmen in ventral view; I. hind wings; J. tegmina. Scales: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5683484" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5683484/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="556">Fig. 6H</figureCitation>
). Mirror on right tegmina slightly longer than wide (
<figureCitation box="[1181,1247,1872,1899]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1651,1675]" captionTargetBox="[196,1390,240,1619]" captionTargetId="figure-40@7.[189,1398,234,1625]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 6. Head, thorax and wings of Ptosoproctus baishishanicus sp. nov. A, B, D, E–H. male; C, I, J. female. A. face; B. head and pronotum in dorsal view; C. pronotum and tegmen in lateral view; D. thorax in ventral view; E. left tegmen in dorsal view; F, right tegmen in dorsal view; G. left tegmen in ventral view; H. right tegmen in ventral view; I. hind wings; J. tegmina. Scales: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5683484" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5683484/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="556">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
FH). Hind wings rudimentary (
<figureCitation box="[303,381,1908,1935]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1651,1675]" captionTargetBox="[196,1390,240,1619]" captionTargetId="figure-40@7.[189,1398,234,1625]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 6. Head, thorax and wings of Ptosoproctus baishishanicus sp. nov. A, B, D, E–H. male; C, I, J. female. A. face; B. head and pronotum in dorsal view; C. pronotum and tegmen in lateral view; D. thorax in ventral view; E. left tegmen in dorsal view; F, right tegmen in dorsal view; G. left tegmen in ventral view; H. right tegmen in ventral view; I. hind wings; J. tegmina. Scales: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5683484" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5683484/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="556">Fig. 6I</figureCitation>
). Fore tibiae dorsally armed 2–3 external spines and internally unarmed. Middle tibiae dorsally with 2 external spines and 1–2 internal spines (one at apical). 10 
<superScript attach="left" box="[879,892,1944,1958]" fontSize="6" pageId="8" pageNumber="556">th</superScript>
abdominal tergite fused with epiproct, posterior margin of 10th abdominal tergite with a broadly triangle notch at the joint, form a down-folded membranous projection on tergite posterior margin, projection with a gourd-shaped median longitudinal furrow, apex broadly rounded. Cercus conical, pileous, short and stout, external margin straight; apex short and obtusely conical; inner tooth near cercus apex, robust, recurved and slightly incurve, apical part suddenly narrowly, apex acutely (
<figureCitation box="[1251,1319,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1694,1718]" captionTargetBox="[193,1393,638,1661]" captionTargetId="figure-244@8.[189,1398,630,1667]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 7. Abdominal apex of Ptosoproctus baishishanicus sp. nov. A–E. male; F–H. female. A, F. dorsal view; B. lateral view; C, G. ventral view; D. rear view; E. titillators; H. ovipositor. Scales: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5683486" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5683486/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="557">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
AB). Subgenital plate length as long as wide, with lateral carinae, middle part of posterior margin with a triangular excision, styli slender and short (
<figureCitation box="[410,498,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1694,1718]" captionTargetBox="[193,1393,638,1661]" captionTargetId="figure-244@8.[189,1398,630,1667]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 7. Abdominal apex of Ptosoproctus baishishanicus sp. nov. A–E. male; F–H. female. A, F. dorsal view; B. lateral view; C, G. ventral view; D. rear view; E. titillators; H. ovipositor. Scales: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5683486" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5683486/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="557">Fig. 7C</figureCitation>
). Titillators with short apical arms, dorsally bearing one row of denticles; basal arms broad, with a right-angle curve on middle part (
<figureCitation box="[683,770,295,321]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1694,1718]" captionTargetBox="[193,1393,638,1661]" captionTargetId="figure-244@8.[189,1398,630,1667]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 7. Abdominal apex of Ptosoproctus baishishanicus sp. nov. A–E. male; F–H. female. A, F. dorsal view; B. lateral view; C, G. ventral view; D. rear view; E. titillators; H. ovipositor. Scales: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5683486" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5683486/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="557">Fig. 7E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
