<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,150,1257]" pageId="11" pageNumber="559">
Female. Tegmina slightly shorter than half pronotum, extending to 1 
<superScript attach="left" box="[955,968,150,164]" fontSize="6" pageId="11" pageNumber="559">th</superScript>
abdominal tergite anterior margin, clearly visible and discontiguous in dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[635,704,187,214]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1651,1675]" captionTargetBox="[196,1390,240,1619]" captionTargetId="figure-40@7.[189,1398,234,1625]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 6. Head, thorax and wings of Ptosoproctus baishishanicus sp. nov. A, B, D, E–H. male; C, I, J. female. A. face; B. head and pronotum in dorsal view; C. pronotum and tegmen in lateral view; D. thorax in ventral view; E. left tegmen in dorsal view; F, right tegmen in dorsal view; G. left tegmen in ventral view; H. right tegmen in ventral view; I. hind wings; J. tegmina. Scales: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5683484" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5683484/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="559">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
CJ). Fore tibiae dorsally armed 3 external spines and internally unarmed. Middle tibiae dorsally with 4 internal spines (one at apical) and 2 external spines. Cercus conical and hirsute (
<figureCitation box="[242,327,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1694,1718]" captionTargetBox="[193,1393,638,1661]" captionTargetId="figure-244@8.[189,1398,630,1667]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 7. Abdominal apex of Ptosoproctus baishishanicus sp. nov. A–E. male; F–H. female. A, F. dorsal view; B. lateral view; C, G. ventral view; D. rear view; E. titillators; H. ovipositor. Scales: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5683486" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5683486/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="559">Fig. 7F</figureCitation>
). 10th abdominal tergite partly fused with epiproct, posterior margin of 10th abdominal tergite with a broadly round notch at the joint (
<figureCitation box="[546,632,295,321]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1694,1718]" captionTargetBox="[193,1393,638,1661]" captionTargetId="figure-244@8.[189,1398,630,1667]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 7. Abdominal apex of Ptosoproctus baishishanicus sp. nov. A–E. male; F–H. female. A, F. dorsal view; B. lateral view; C, G. ventral view; D. rear view; E. titillators; H. ovipositor. Scales: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5683486" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5683486/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="559">Fig. 7F</figureCitation>
). Subgenital plate wider than length, middle of posterior margin with a deep angle concave (
<figureCitation box="[386,476,331,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1694,1718]" captionTargetBox="[193,1393,638,1661]" captionTargetId="figure-244@8.[189,1398,630,1667]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 7. Abdominal apex of Ptosoproctus baishishanicus sp. nov. A–E. male; F–H. female. A, F. dorsal view; B. lateral view; C, G. ventral view; D. rear view; E. titillators; H. ovipositor. Scales: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5683486" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5683486/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="559">Fig. 7G</figureCitation>
). Ovipositor shorter than hind femora, distinctly upcurved (
<figureCitation box="[1143,1233,331,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1694,1718]" captionTargetBox="[193,1393,638,1661]" captionTargetId="figure-244@8.[189,1398,630,1667]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 7. Abdominal apex of Ptosoproctus baishishanicus sp. nov. A–E. male; F–H. female. A, F. dorsal view; B. lateral view; C, G. ventral view; D. rear view; E. titillators; H. ovipositor. Scales: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5683486" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5683486/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="559">Fig. 7H</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,150,1257]" pageId="11" pageNumber="559">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,366,392]" pageId="11" pageNumber="559">Coloration.</emphasis>
Body laterally and dorsally generally dark brown, with whitish gray and dark green marmoration, ventrally mint green. Lower and hind margin of pronotum lateral lobes whitish gray with dark brown spots. Tegmina orange. Spines of each leg black. Male cercus inner tooth black. Ovipositor apical part black.
</paragraph>
